File: A golf ball. CAPE TOWN - The SunBet Cape Town Ladies Open tees off this week and South Africa’s leading golfers will aim for the main prize. This year’s purse has doubled to R400,000 thanks to new sponsors. Local talents will battle it out with the first international campaigners. The event has been hosted in the Mother City for the past six years. Three-time winner Lee-Anne Pace will spearhead the local charge.